5000|$|The [...] "zero of longitude" [...] of galactic {{coordinates}} {{was also}} defined in 1959 {{to be at}} position angle 123° from the north celestial pole. Thus the zero longitude point on the <b>galactic</b> <b>equator</b> was at , [...] (B1950) or , [...] (J2000), and its J2000 position angle is 122.932°. The galactic center is located at position angle 31.72° (B1950) or 31.40° (J2000) east of north.|$|E
